Dataset source : https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/thedevastator/airbnb-prices-in-european-cities

Audience : Airbnb Host

Story : Identify determinants of Airbnb listing prices across 10 Europen cities for Hosts to plan optimally for upcoming/existing listing strategy yielding higher revenue.

## Loading required package: kableExtra
## corrplot 0.92 loaded

  The above visual shows overview of number of Airbnb listings, Average listing price, Number of Business listings, Super hosts listing for 10 different European cities. 
  
  
  

The correlation chart above shows that having more bedrooms in an Airbnb listing is slightly related to having a higher listing price, but the relationship is not very strong. There doesn't seem to be a clear relationship between the other factors and the listing price.
Cleanliness rating has 0.7 with guest rating which could improve number booking count.

The chart indicates that Airbnb listing prices are observed increasing gradually for bedroom counts from 0 to 3. Only Barcelona, Lisbon, Berlin have listings with 5 or more bedrooms, with lower prices for the offerings. Assumed factors to lower prices for properties with more bedrooms could be locality, neighbourhood or ratings. 



The next determinant factor we can check for Airbnb prices could be Superhost for a listing. Lets see if superhost has impact on listing prices. Below is the proportion of Airbnb with SuperHost and No SuperHost listing across 10 cities in Europe.

Lets compare listing price with Super hosts and without superhosts below. The scatterplot charts suggests that whether a listing has a superhost or not does not have a significant impact on the listing price, as both types of listings fall in the same price range for each city. Therefore, it can be concluded that there is no clear relationship between having a superhost and higher listing prices. Hence, Superhost would not be a good choice to strategize prices of an Airbnb property but having superhosts could lead to more booking eventually higher revenues.

Usually, the listing prices of Airbnb properties generally differ based on their proximity to prime areas or distance from the city center.

 For most cities, the chart suggests that listing prices tend to be higher for properties located closer to the city center. However, this trend is not observed in Lisbon and Vienna, where the difference in listing prices between prime and non-prime areas is not significant. Having an Airbnb property located in the vicinity of prime areas can be advantageous for achieving higher prices except for Lisbon and Vienna cities.

Overall rating do not indicate higher prices of Airbnb. Hence Airbnb properties with higher overall rating could definitely attract more bookings.

The chart suggests that airbnb for business purpose have higher prices as compared to non business purpose properties for most of the cities except for Budapest, Lisbon, Amsterdam cities. Hence, Business properties in selective cities could be a optmial way to list properties with  higher prices. 



  Time of week as determinant for the Listing prices of airbnb properties across 10 cities. 

  The chart suggest that prices are higher on weekends for cities like Amsterdam, Budapest due to tourism. Hence, Host can modify prices for weekend for optimal profitability.
  


Conclusion : 
1. To offer Airbnb properties at higher prices host can consider the factors like property situated at prime location of city, listing property for business purposes.
2. Strategy to increase number of bookings Host can focus on determinants like having a Superhost, trying to get good customer ratings.
